Well, at least you don't have cooties like me. I watched this and another video but don't have much strength and slept 15 hours or so. My father gave me coronavirus maybe, as he's in the hospital with it. But on a good note, you can edit videos on your Samsung S10+ with Adobe Rush. I've done that on my S10 and it rocks. You're a pro I'm sure you could do rather well with it. $10 a month and there's into online for doing it etc. I hope your camera is ok. Doesn't look waterproof. Might want to stick to your S10+ it's waterproof like my S10. I used to shower with my phone when expecting important calls or listening to music before I set up my Amazon Echo Dot to play music. And for power here's this: https://litsolar.com/products/wireless-lit-solar-powerbank I don't have it but I have a similar one, not as awesome and from another company but very very useful. It has solar panels and can charge my phone wirelessly. Comes in handy if the charge port gets wet. Stay dry! 🙏🖖📖 And don't forget about ebooks!
